    <description>Peasy is a middle tier micro-framework that offers an easy to use and flexible rules engine and was designed to address common challenges such as threading, concurrency, scalability, fault tolerance, async and multiple client support</description>
    <releaseNotes>
      - THIS IS A SIGNIFICANT VERSION UPGRADE AND CONTAINS POTENTIAL BREAKING CHANGES
      - Separates asynchronous and synchronous operations into their own first-class citizens.
      - Introduces IRulesSuccessorContainer, IRuleSuccessor, ISupportCommandValidation.
      - Renames many method and parameter names for better uniformity and parity across the framework.
      - Adds better code documentation.
      - Adds runtime debugger support via symbol packaging.
      - Repurposes IRulesContainer and PeasyException.
      - REMOVES: Overly opinionated attributes, classes, extensions, interfaces, and rules that are better suited outside of the core framework.
    </releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright 2021</copyright>
    <tags>Middle, Tier, Framework, Business, Logic, Layer</tags>
    <summary>An easy to use middle tier framework for .NET and .NET Core</summary>
